org.orgDesc: A student community supported by Google Developers aims to equip students with technical skills through hands-on projects, coding workshops, and mentorship programs especially mobile and web development, cloud computing, and AI.

reviewText: I recently had the opportunity to engage with Google Developer Groups Open Community (GDGOC), and I must say, my experience has been nothing short of inspiring. Whether you're a beginner eager to learn the fundamentals of software development or an experienced professional looking to network and share knowledge, GDGOC provides a welcoming environment where innovation and collaboration thrive. One of the standout features of GDGOC is its well-organized events and workshops. They host a diverse range of technical sessions, hackathons, and coding boot camps covering topics like Android Development, Web Technologies, Cloud Computing, Machine Learning, and AI. I attended one of their Google Cloud Workshops, where experienced mentors walked us through real-world applications of cloud computing. The session was hands-on, interactive, and highly informative, helping me understand cloud deployment strategies in a way that online courses never could. In addition, their DevFest events are truly world-class.

org.orgDesc: The premier organization for computer science and technology enthusiasts at DLSU. LSCS provides workshops, coding competitions, and networking opportunities for students interested in software development, cybersecurity, and emerging tech

reviewText: The coding boot camps were great, but I wish they had more hands-on activities.
responseMessage: Thanks for the feedback! We'll add more coding challenges in future events.

org.orgDesc: The go-to organization for data science and analytics enthusiasts at DLSU. DSS provides training in machine learning, big data, and statistical analysis, preparing students for careers in data-driven industries.

reviewText: DSS has a great data science community, but the workshops are sometimes too advanced for beginners.
